Detailed Description

This table holds the calendar-specific information.

Each row in this table contains the details for a single calendar, such as the name, color, sync information, and so on.

static const base::String gaia::content::CalendarInfos::Calendars::_SYNC_ID ( ) [static]

The unique ID for a row assigned by the sync source.

NULL if the row has never been synced. This is used as a reference id for exceptions along with _ID.

Type: TEXT

static const base::String gaia::content::CalendarInfos::Calendars::ACCOUNT_NAME ( ) [static]

The account that was used to sync the entry to the device.

If the account_type is not "LOCAL" then the name and type must match an account on the device or the calendar will be deleted.

Type: TEXT

static const base::String gaia::content::CalendarInfos::Calendars::ACCOUNT_TYPE ( ) [static]

The type of the account that was used to sync the entry to the device.

A type of "LOCAL" will keep this event form being deleted if there are no matching accounts on the device.

Type: TEXT

static const base::String gaia::content::CalendarInfos::Calendars::ALLOWED_ATTENDEE_TYPES ( ) [static]

A comma separated list of attendee types supported for this calendar in the format "#,#,#".

Valid types are gaia::content::CalendarEvents#TYPE_NONE, gaia::content::CalendarEvents#TYPE_OPTIONAL, gaia::content::CalendarEvents#TYPE_REQUIRED, gaia::content::CalendarEvents#TYPE_RESOURCE. Setting this field to only gaia::content::CalendarEvents#TYPE_NONE should be used to indicate that changing the attendee type is not supported.

static const base::String gaia::content::CalendarInfos::Calendars::ALLOWED_AVAILABILITY ( ) [static]

A comma separated list of availability types supported for this calendar in the format "#,#,#".

Valid types are gaia::content::CalendarEvents#AVAILABILITY_BUSY, gaia::content::CalendarEvents#AVAILABILITY_FREE, gaia::content::CalendarEvents#AVAILABILITY_TENTATIVE. Setting this field to only gaia::content::CalendarEvents#AVAILABILITY_BUSY should be used to indicate that changing the availability is not supported.

static const base::String gaia::content::CalendarInfos::Calendars::ALLOWED_REMINDERS ( ) [static]

A comma separated list of reminder methods supported for this calendar in the format "#,#,#".

Valid types are: METHOD_DEFAULT = 0; METHOD_ALERT = 1; METHOD_EMAIL = 2; METHOD_SMS = 3;

Type: TEXT

static const base::String gaia::content::CalendarInfos::Calendars::CALENDAR_ACCESS_LEVEL ( ) [static]

The level of access that the user has for the calendar 0 = Cannot access the calendar.

100 = Can only see free/busy information about the calendar. 200 = Can read all event details. 300 = Can reply yes/no/maybe to an event. 400 = not used. 500 = Full access to modify the calendar, but not the access control settings. 600 = Full access to modify the calendar, but not the access control settings. 700 = Full access to the calendar. 800 = Domain admin.

Type: INTEGER (one of the values below)

static const base::String gaia::content::CalendarInfos::Calendars::CALENDAR_COLOR ( ) [static]

The color of the calendar.

This should only be updated by the sync adapter, not other apps, as changing a calendar's color can adversely affect its display.

Type: INTEGER (color value)

static const base::String gaia::content::CalendarInfos::Calendars::CALENDAR_COLOR_KEY ( ) [static]

A key for looking up a color from the Colors table.

NULL or an empty string are reserved for indicating that the calendar does not use a key for looking up the color. The provider will update CALENDAR_COLOR automatically when a valid key is written to this column. The key must reference an existing row of the Colors table.

Type: TEXT

static const base::String gaia::content::CalendarInfos::Calendars::CAN_PARTIALLY_UPDATE ( ) [static]

If set to 1 this causes events on this calendar to be duplicated with CalendarEvents::Events#LAST_SYNCED set to 1 whenever the event transitions from non-dirty to dirty.

The duplicated event will not be expanded in the instances table and will only show up in sync adapter queries of the events table. It will also be deleted when the originating event has its dirty flag cleared by the sync adapter.

Type: INTEGER (boolean)
